![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2605aa2c-19b2-4c85-bb89-82b9fe3fffd4/ep241.jpg?format=original)

Can you believe it's been 60 years since everyone’s friendly neighborhood spider-man came thwipping into the comic book scene and into our hearts? Hands down one of the greatest superheroes of all time, Spidey has managed to stand the test of time, mostly because of the great foundation that was laid when the character was first introduced in 1962. Join us as we review Spider-Man's debut in Amazing Fantasy #15, talk about the character’s staying power, and discuss our first introduction to the webhead in this fun look back at the creation of a true legend in the superhero realm! 

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
